<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-14T14:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-14T14:36:00-05:00" n="930" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13507.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Canova</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aguascalientes</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-14T13:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 14, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The temporary organization of the convention, adjourned from Mexico City,
                            was made permanent last night and the Military Contention declared its
                            sovereignty. The Convention will not take up the question of the First
                            Chief until Zapata is fully represented.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canova</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>